<div class="min-h-screen pt-14 pb-10 relative" style="background: transparent;">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
    <div class="mb-6">
      <%= link_to root_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 btn btn-secondary group" do %>
        <span class="material-icons transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform">arrow_back</span>
        <span>Back to Home</span>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <article class="glass-thick rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12">
      <header class="mb-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Fun Links</h1>
        <p class="text-lg" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">A curated list of fun, inspiring, or experimental things.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Coding Games</h2>
          <div class="grid gap-6">
            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "CodinGame",
                    "https://www.codingame.com/",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                When I need a break from work code, I jump into CodinGame. Nothing like building an AI bot to play games for you. The community solutions are always humbling - there's always a more elegant approach.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "CSS Grid Garden",
                    "https://cssgridgarden.com/",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                Yeah, I'm a backend dev, but I still need to wrangle CSS sometimes. This game actually made grid layouts click for me. Way better than reading MDN docs for the hundredth time.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "Ruby Warrior",
                    "https://www.bloc.io/ruby-warrior",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                Program a warrior to fight through a tower using Ruby. It starts simple but gets tricky fast. Great for when you want to practice Ruby fundamentals in a fun way.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "Elevator Saga",
                    "http://play.elevatorsaga.com/",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                This one's addictive. You program elevator logic in JavaScript to move people efficiently. I spent way too long optimizing my solution for level 4. Good practice for thinking about queuing algorithms.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">AI Exploration</h2>
          <div class="grid gap-6">
            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "OpenAI Playground",
                    "https://platform.openai.com/playground",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                I use this to experiment with different prompts and understand how these models actually work. It's fascinating to tweak the temperature settings and see how it affects outputs.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "Hugging Face Spaces",
                    "https://huggingface.co/spaces",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                The community here is building some wild stuff. I love browsing through the demos - gives me ideas for side projects. The image generation models are particularly fun to play with.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "Replicate",
                    "https://replicate.com/explore",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                When I want to run ML models without dealing with infrastructure, Replicate is my go-to. Their API is dead simple - perfect for prototyping ideas quickly.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

